	git add .
git commit -m "Initial backup"
	git commit -m "Initial backup"
git push -u origin master
	git push -u origin master
	
4) Add the following to a macro or printer.cfg file

[gcode_shell_command backup_to_github]
command: sh /home/pi/backup.sh
timeout: 30.
verbose: True

[gcode_macro GITHUB_BACKUP]
gcode:
    RUN_SHELL_COMMAND CMD=backup_to_github

5) Open WinSCP and connect to your printer
6) Copy the “gcode_shell_command.py”: file into the extras folder.
7) Copy the “backup.sh” file, updated with the correct credentials, into the pi folder.
8) Create a macro button to run the backup.